gw.api.admin

Class ImportDataArrayDifferences

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.admin.ImportDataArrayDifferences

  • public class ImportDataArrayDifferences
extends Object
    Represents the differences between the imported and the original values of a particular array field on an entity. Used after importing data to display differences in an array to the user.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      Bean[] AddedElements
      The elements added to the array by the import.
      String[] OrderedFieldNames
      A sorted array of the field names present on elements of the array. Excludes a few internal fields that should not be exposed to the user (such as the creation date, internal id and so on).
      Bean[] RemovedElements
      The elements removed from the array by the import.

      • Fields inherited from class java.lang.Object

        Class

    • Constructor Summary

      ImportDataArrayDifferences(IEntityPropertyInfo field, KeyableBean owner)
      Constructs a new ImportDataArrayDifferences object for the given array field on the given entity. The entity is assumed to have been modified by a data import.
